<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Keeping Score in Scrabble</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">English Solver · 2-letter words</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Accurate scorekeeping is fundamental to Scrabble — a single miscounted tile or missed premium square can change who wins. This guide covers the complete scoring system, from basic letter values to endgame adjustments and common mistakes that cost players points.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Letter Point Values</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">0 pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">Blank</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">1 pt</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">A E I L N O R S T U</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">2 pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">D G</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">3 pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">B C M P</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">4 pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">F H V W Y</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">5 pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">K</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">8 pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">J X</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">10 pts</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">Q Z</span></span>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Premium Square Rules</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Square</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Effect</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Count</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Key Rule</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-blue-400">DL</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Double letter value</td><td class="px-4 py-3">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only the covering tile</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-blue-600">TL</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Triple letter value</td><td class="px-4 py-3">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only the covering tile</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-pink-400">DW</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Double word score</td><td class="px-4 py-3">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3">After letter multipliers</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-red-400">TW</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Triple word score</td><td class="px-4 py-3">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3">After letter multipliers</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Rule</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Premium squares only apply on the <span class="text-white font-medium">first turn they are covered</span>. Once a tile sits on a premium square, it scores at face value for all subsequent words that include it.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Scoring Order of Operations</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Step 1:</span> Apply letter multipliers (DL/TL) to individual tiles placed on those squares this turn.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Step 2:</span> Sum all tile values in the word (including already-placed tiles at face value).</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Step 3:</span> Apply word multipliers (DW/TW). If a word covers two DW squares, multiply by 4.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Step 4:</span> Score ALL words formed (including crosswords). Add 50-point bingo bonus if all 7 tiles used.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Scoring Mistakes</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Forgetting crosswords</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">When you form parallel plays, EVERY new word scores separately. Missing a crossword can mean 10-20 lost points.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Reusing premium squares</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A DW square only doubles the word on the turn it's first covered. Later words crossing that tile score it at face value.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Endgame Scoring Adjustments</h2>

<p>When one player uses all their tiles, the game ends and final scoring adjustments apply:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Player who goes out:</span> Adds the total face value of all tiles remaining on their opponent's rack to their own score.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Player with tiles left:</span> Subtracts the face value of their remaining tiles from their own score. This double penalty can swing results by 20-40 points.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">If both players pass:</span> When the game ends because both players pass (or 6 consecutive zero-score turns), each player subtracts their own remaining tile values. No one gains the opponent's tiles.</p>
  </div>
</div>

